10: Nice job, Reticia! It came out perfect!
14:
I couldn't have done it without you.
Seriously. I'm used to leaving the
cooking to the maids.
17:
I'm just happy I was able to help,
considering how much you've done
for me.
21:
...Well, the real challenge is what
comes next.
26:
You can do it! All you need is a little
courage!
31:
You're the last person I wanna hear
that from!
35:
Hehehe! Sure, it took a lot of help
from everyone, but now I'm happier
than ever before!
38: That's... good to hear, at least.
41:
Actually, you know what Will did
yesterday?
54:
W-we just did what any normal
couple would do! I think!
57:
He just made me feel... You know...
Ehehe...
64:
Y-yeah? From what Nate told me,
you're no different!
66:
You had the wildest fantasy going
through your head during the whole
sheep businessâ€”
82:
Ugh... Mary had to go and put all
those weird thoughts into my head.
86: Reticia, are you here to train too?
90:
Uh, y-yeah, kind of! I see you're
already hard at work.
93:
Just trying to be prepared, since you
never know when a fight will break
out. Besides, I've gotta make sure I
don't fall behind.
100:
How about a spar? We can see what
the training's been doing for you.
103: ...Just don't go too hard on me, okay?
109:
Hehe, I'd call that a definite win for
me today.
114:
Sheesh... I might've stood a chance if
we weren't using weapons...
118:
Hm, you think so? If you ask me, the
bigger problem is that we started
when you were already tired from
your other exercises.
122:
Eh, it's good practice. I don't expect
to fight every battle completely
rested.
128:
Here. This should give you a boost of
energy.
131:
I made this chocolate just for you.
It's different from the ones I gave
everyone else.
146:
...A-anyway, it's about time for me to
go. S-see you around!
150: Oh? Did we come at a bad time?
167:
I guess not. Do you not like the
chocolate she gave you?
178:
So? Does that mean you're happy
she gave you something special?
186:
Come on. I know your heart's not
made of stone.
191:
I-I mean... Who wouldn't be happy?
She's pretty cute! You guys have
eyes, don't you?
195:
Kinda hard not to appreciate it
when someone dresses up on your
behalf, yeah?
200:
It took everything in me to keep it
together this whole time! Is that
what you wanted to hear? Now
leave me aloneâ€”
219:
I accidentally left my guns behind,
and when I came back to grab
them, I couldn't help but overhear...
223:
So this whole time you were actually
super happy?
227:
O-okay, hold on... What you heard
just now was like... more a result of
stress than anything...
237:
Why apologize? I'm pretty happy,
you know.
239:
Even though you accepted the
chocolate, I was worried that maybe
I was being a bother.
242:
Listen, you'd never be a bother. You
should be more confident in yourself.
247:
I don't want a lesson in self-worth
from you of all people!
251:
Besides, you could've told me you
like me back and then everything
would've been fine!
259:
Hmph. I'll let you off the hook for
today.
262:
But someday, I swear I'll make you
say it!
